# A destructuring `map [:x :y] in <expr>` binder lives only within its own comprehension body:
# reads of `:x`/`:y` inside the body (line 2) resolve cleanly, but a read of `:x` after the
# comprehension closes (line 3) has no visible declaration in scope (spec/grammar.md:136-137;
# spec/execution-model.md:317-327).
:pairs = [[1 2]]
:doubled = map [:x :y] in :pairs [ :x + :y ]
print :x
